(108, 1, '2013-04-22 12:00:35', '2013-04-22 12:00:35', '', 'Fixed price', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'fixed-price', '', '', '2013-04-22 12:00:35', '2013-04-22 12:00:35', '', 0, 'http://192.168.1.220:8086/mbt/products-page/uncategorized/', 0, 'wpsc-product', '', 0),
(110, 1, '2013-04-25 06:53:01', '2013-04-25 06:53:01', 'What are Electronic Health Records (EHRs)? Electronic information is transforming most industries today. Electronic health is the technology of communicating, processing, and deriving information in electronic form via EHRs. Electronic information will continue to impact healthcare industry and how each market participant functions within the marketplace. What has already changed? What will continue to change? Today’s electronic health initiatives implement new forms of electronic communication and processing tools in our current healthcare system. This course is designed to provide an introduction to the world of Electronic Health Records and their role in electronic health and our healthcare system. ', 'Introduction to Auditing Electronic Health Records', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'introduction-to-auditing-electronic-health-records', '', '', '2013-04-25 06:53:01', '2013-04-25 06:53:01', '', 0, 'http://192.168.1.220:8086/mbt/?post_type=question&#038;p=110', 0, 'question', '', 0),
(111, 1, '2013-04-25 06:53:37', '2013-04-25 06:53:37', 'During the past 100 years, we have witnessed significant advancements in healthcare delivery systems. Today, a true electronic health environment has the ability to derive data intelligence on an almost real-time basis and presents unprecedented opportunities to benefit individuals and communities. This course is designed to provide industry application of Electronic Health Records within two frameworks: the users of health information and the market standards. To fully appreciate and audit the users of health information, it is first important to have a process to identify each and every user. As the market evolves and new standards for building and utilizing electronic health systems emerge, auditors will also need to include these standards within their audit scope', 'Auditing Electronic Health Records: Industry Applications', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'auditing-electronic-health-records-industry-applications', '', '', '2013-04-25 06:53:44', '2013-04-25 06:53:44', '', 0, 'http://192.168.1.220:8086/mbt/?post_type=question&#038;p=111', 0, 'question', '', 0),
